# Core apps are SNAPSHOTS of their catalog repos. The catalog repo is the
# single source of truth; core-apps/<slug>/ is a committed copy of it, baked
# into the image and installed at boot by install-core-apps.sh.
#
# To update a built-in app: edit it in its catalog repo (mobius-os/app-<slug>),
# bump the commit below, run `scripts/sync-core-apps.sh`, and commit the diff.
# CI (`scripts/check-core-apps-sync.sh`) fails the build if core-apps/<slug>
# drifts from <repo>@<commit> — so the two trees can never silently diverge
# again (which is how core-apps/reflection once shipped without its manifest).
#
# NATIVE apps: a core app may instead be authored directly in this repo with no
# catalog repo (none at present). Such apps are simply NOT listed below —
# they have no upstream to diff against, so the sync check skips them. Their
# manifest is still required: tests/test_core_apps_manifests.py enforces that
# EVERY core-apps/<slug>/ ships a valid mobius.json, native or not.
#
# Format (catalog-synced apps only): <slug>  <owner/repo>  <commit-sha>
memory      mobius-os/app-memory      2d64d3c7d5baeb0443ad527632e142ab164cff78
reflection  mobius-os/app-reflection  da0557ba257058c1bd01f73983519c52c0d2f21b
beat-machine  mobius-os/app-beat-machine  b23ee738d557389c6eeab408117574859926ff1c
